MINIMAL FIX (PRIMARY) — SITE: rm_get_adapter_status, /root/open-gpu-kernel-modules/src/nvidia/arch/nvalloc/unix/src/osapi.c:2744-2761. Deep-RM placement is JUSTIFIED-MINIMAL (identical to where C1/A10 already edit osapi.c) because the blocking acquire is physically in this deep-RM function; there is no kernel-open seam that wraps it. Change the acquire flags from blocking READ to conditional, and ROUTE it through the eGPU gate so dGPU behavior is byte-for-byte unchanged. Code sketch (A11):

  NV_STATUS rm_get_adapter_status(nv_state_t *pNv, NvU32 *pStatus) {
      NV_STATUS rmStatus = NV_ERR_OPERATING_SYSTEM;
      NvU32 apiFlags = RMAPI_LOCK_FLAGS_READ;
      // A11 (F45): on an external GPU, the deferred-open worker reaches this
      // on the cold-init FAILURE arm (nv.c rm_get_adapter_status_external).
      // A blocking acquire here (READ is stripped to WRITE for OSAPI, rmapi.c:578)
      // parks the single-threaded nv_open_q worker behind a held lock, wedging
      // the close wait (open_complete) and the pciehp open_q flush -> F45 deadlock.
      // adapter_status is best-effort telemetry; on contention return the same
      // NV_ERR_OPERATING_SYSTEM the function already defaults to.
      if (pNv != NULL && pNv->is_external_gpu)
          apiFlags |= API_LOCK_FLAGS_COND_ACQUIRE;
      if (rmapiLockAcquire(apiFlags, RM_LOCK_MODULES_OSAPI) == NV_OK) {
          rmStatus = RmGetAdapterStatus(pNv, pStatus);
          rmapiLockRelease();
      }
      return rmStatus;
  }

FAILURE-PATH CORRECTNESS (the COND must abort cleanly): when COND_ACQUIRE write fails, rmapiLockAcquire returns NV_ERR_TIMEOUT_RETRY WITHOUT blocking (verified rmapi.c:605-612, write-conditional branch). rm_get_adapter_status then skips the body and returns its initialized NV_ERR_OPERATING_SYSTEM (osapi.c:2749). The sole caller rm_get_adapter_status_external folds ANY non-NV_OK to NV_ERR_OPERATING_SYSTEM already (osapi.c:2773-2776), so adapter_status = NV_ERR_OPERATING_SYSTEM — bit-identical to the genuinely-contended/lost case. nv_open_device_for_nvlfp (nv.c:1779-1790) sees open_rc still non-zero (init already failed) and returns it unchanged. NO retry loop is added: the deferred worker MUST NOT spin on TIMEOUT_RETRY (that would re-introduce a busy-wait against the same lock the flush needs to drain); a single best-effort attempt is exactly the right semantic for telemetry. Net: zero stranded state, worker proceeds to complete_all.

